def: A cloud formation similar to cirro-stratus, but heavier and ata lower level.

Any one of several species of edible marine fishes belonging tothe genus Trachinus, of the family Trachinid√¶. They have a broadspinose head, with the eyes looking upward. The long dorsal fin issupported by numerous strong, sharp spines which cause painfulwounds.
To charge upon with reproach; to upbraid. [R.] Sir T. Browne.
A colorless, crystalline substance extracted from oil ofcloves; -- called also clove camphor.
The basal part of the labium of insects. It bears the mentum.
A kind of beer. Same as Quass.
Generous; liberal; munificent.-- O"pen-hand`ed*ness, n. J. S. Mill.
A liquid hydrocarbon obtained by the dry distillation oftropine with quicklime. It is regarded as being homologous withdipropargyl.
Any bryozoan of the genus Flustra or allied genera which formfrondlike corals.
A curve traced by the end of a string wound upon another curve,or unwound from it; -- called also evolvent. See Evolute.
